{"timestamp": "2025-12-07 02:15:09.133684", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nScope and topology\\n- Fabric: Multi-tier EBGP Clos (super-spine AS 65000, spines AS 651xx, leaves AS 652xx), interconnects on 172.16.0.0/16 (/31 links), host subnets 10.<pod>.<leaf>.0/24.\\n- Path under test (explicitly): pc_0_0 ↔ leaf_router_0_0 ↔ spine_router_0_0/spine_router_0_1 ↔ super_spine_router_0 ↔ … ↔ leaf_router_0_1 ↔ pc_0_1.\\n\\nKey checks performed\\n1) End-to-end reachability\\n- Broad fabric reachability sampling shows 0% loss across many cross-pod host pairs with RTT ~1–5 ms.\\n- Targeted: pc_0_0 → pc_0_1 and pc_0_1 → pc_0_0 both succeed (4/4, 0% loss), RTT avg ~2.6–3.3 ms.\\nAssessment: Data plane forwarding between leaves through the spine/super-spine layers is healthy; no loss or excessive latency.\\n\\n2) Control-plane (BGP) health\\n- leaf_router_0_0 (AS 65200) and leaf_router_0_1 (AS 65201):\\n  - BGP summary: 8 neighbors each, all Established; PfxRcd ~31; PfxSnt ~32.\\n  - RIB/FIB: Connected host /24 present; all other 10.x/24 learned via BGP pointing to spine uplink (e.g., 172.16.1.0 or 172.16.1.2).\\n- spine_router_0_0 (AS 65100) and spine_router_0_1 (AS 65101):\\n  - BGP summary: 12 neighbors each (super-spines + leaves), all Established.\\n  - PfxRcd from each leaf neighbor aligns with expectation (spine learns the single /24 from each leaf). PfxSnt to leaves shows full fabric reachability (dozens of /24s).\\n  - RIB/FIB: Per-destination next-hops to local leaves; ECMP to remote pods via multiple super-spine uplinks is present.\\n- super_spine_router_0 (AS 65000):\\n  - BGP summary: 32 neighbors, all Established.\\n  - RIB/FIB: Aggregated reachability to all 10.x/24s via appropriate spine next-hops; direct EBGP adjacencies to all spines are up.\\nAssessment: BGP sessions are stable (no Idle/Active, no flaps observed), prefix exchange consistent with full-fabric reachability, and forwarding tables reflect expected next-hops at each tier.\\n\\n3) Data-plane routing consistency\\n- Leaves: Have connected host /24 and BGP routes for all other host /24s via a spine uplink; forwarding symmetry acceptable for Clos design.\\n- Spines: Show ECMP for remote pods via multiple super-spine peers.\\n- Super-spine: Holds full visibility to pod /24s with next-hops toward the corresponding spines.\\n\\nAnomalies detected\\n- No loss, no unreachable paths, and no BGP neighbor down states observed.\\n- Route-population and next-hop selection are consistent with the design and provide full reachability across pods.\\n\\nNoteworthy observations (non-blocking)\\n- Leaves install a single best BGP path to remote /24s (no leaf-side ECMP visible). This can be a design choice and is not impacting connectivity; spines are performing ECMP upstream.\\n- Prefix counters vary by role (e.g., spines send many prefixes to leaves; leaves receive many and send few). Observed numbers align with expectations for this EBGP Clos fabric.\\n\\nLocalization and root cause\\n- Fault localization: No faulty devices or links identified along the pc_0_0 ↔ pc_0_1 path or within the sampled fabric.\\n- Root cause: Not applicable—no anomaly or service degradation detected.\\n\\nOverall assessment\\n- The data center Clos fabric is operating normally:\\n  - All critical EBGP adjacencies are Established and exchanging expected prefixes.\\n  - End-to-end connectivity between hosts (including pc_0_0 and pc_0_1) is lossless with low latency.\\n  - Forwarding entries at leaves, spines, and super-spine are consistent and comprehensive., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='31fe50b3-90a3-4988-9711-6878a5e55fd2'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
